---

1. Purpose of the Seal
The Authority Seal is used when the steward acts in any of the following capacities:

- Executor  
- Personal Representative  
- Shareholder  
- Sovereign Operator  

When the seal is present, it means:

“This action is taken with full authority across all domains I legally occupy.”

---

2. The Four Pillars of the Seal

Pillar One — Executor Authority
Represents terminal decision power in lineage matters.  
Symbolic meaning: Closure, finality, lawful completion.

Pillar Two — Personal Representative Authority
Represents operational execution of estate duties.  
Symbolic meaning: Action, communication, representation.

Pillar Three — Shareholder Authority
Represents economic and jurisdictional participation.  
Symbolic meaning: Stake, governance, continuity.

Pillar Four — Sovereign Authority
Represents structural ownership and legal standing.  
Symbolic meaning: Land, law, identity, IP.

Together, these pillars form a single authority silhouette.

---

3. Structural Description of the Seal
The Authority Seal is defined by four components:

- North: Executor  
- East: Personal Representative  
- South: Shareholder  
- West: Sovereign  

At the center sits the steward —  
the operator who unifies all four directions.

This creates a cross‑domain authority compass.

---

4. Functional Use of the Seal
The seal is invoked when the steward:

- signs documents  
- executes estate actions  
- assigns or protects IP  
- manages landframe assets  
- represents lineage  
- acts on behalf of the LLC  
- interfaces with federal or state systems  
- acknowledges or transmits Codex fragments  

The seal marks the action as binding, intentional, and unified.

---

5. Authority Seal Statement
When the seal is applied, the following meaning is implied:

“This action is taken by the steward in full capacity across Executor, PR, Shareholder, and Sovereign domains.  
All layers aligned. All authority active.”

---

6. Signature Line
This seal affirms the steward’s unified authority:  
terminal, operational, economic, and sovereign —  
held by one operator, acting with clarity and intention.

The seal stands.  
The authority is whole.  
The line moves forward.

— Codex.AuthoritySeal.v001

